Character Class Methods

Checking Types of Characters

isLetter(char ch) – Checks if the character is a letter.

isDigit(char ch) – Checks if the character is a digit.

isLetterOrDigit(char ch) – Checks if the character is a letter or digit.

isAlphabetic(int codePoint) – Checks if it’s alphabetic.

isLowerCase(char ch) – Checks if it’s a lowercase letter.

isUpperCase(char ch) – Checks if it’s an uppercase letter.

isWhitespace(char ch) – Checks if it’s a whitespace.

isSpaceChar(char ch) – Checks if it’s a space character.

isISOControl(char ch) – Checks if it’s an ISO control character.

isMirrored(char ch) – Checks if the character has a mirror-image glyph.

Converting Characters

toUpperCase(char ch) – Converts to uppercase.

toLowerCase(char ch) – Converts to lowercase.

toTitleCase(char ch) – Converts to title case.

toString(char ch) – Returns the string representation.

Numeric Values

getNumericValue(char ch) – Returns numeric value (e.g., '3' → 3).

digit(char ch, int radix) – Returns numeric value in given radix.

forDigit(int digit, int radix) – Returns character for digit in given radix.

Code Points and Unicode

codePointAt(CharSequence seq, int index) – Returns Unicode code point.

codePointBefore(CharSequence seq, int index) – Returns previous code point.

codePointCount(CharSequence seq, int beginIndex, int endIndex) – Counts code points.

charCount(int codePoint) – Returns number of char values needed.

toChars(int codePoint) – Converts code point to char array.

isSupplementaryCodePoint(int codePoint) – Checks if supplementary.

isHighSurrogate(char ch) – Checks if high surrogate.

isLowSurrogate(char ch) – Checks if low surrogate.

Other Checks

compare(char x, char y) – Compares two characters.

reverseBytes(char ch) – Reverses the byte order.

isDefined(char ch) – Checks if defined in Unicode.

isIdentifierIgnorable(char ch) – Checks if ignorable in identifier.
